{"event":"pre-tool-use","timestamp":"2026-06-25T14:07:34.342Z","tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"gh pr create --title \"Add Spools page with search, station badges, row tints, and detail navigation\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- New **SpoolsView** at `/spools` — fetches all spools from `GET /api/spools` and renders them in a searchable table\n- Live search filters by spool number, package ID, or station name\n- Each row is tinted by the spool's current station color (purple → Detailing, blue → Cut, coral → Weld, amber → QC, teal → Shipped, green → Installed) for at-a-glance scanning\n- Station column shows a colored badge (dot + label) using the existing `theme.css` design tokens\n- Past-due dates are highlighted in amber (`--color-warning`) rather than red to avoid confusion with error states\n- Advance button calls `POST /api/spools/{id}/advance` and updates the row immediately; `@click.stop` prevents it from also triggering row navigation\n- Clicking any row navigates to the existing `/spools/:id` detail page\n- **QC station color** updated from pink → amber in `theme.css` (light, dark, and `prefers-color-scheme` media query) — pink read as an error/danger state; amber better suits an inspection step\n\n## Reviewer notes\n\n- The `/spools` route is added to the `routes` array (visible in the nav bar); the existing `/spools/:id` detail route stays in `allRoutes` only (no nav entry)\n- `SpoolDetailView.vue` is untouched — this PR only wires navigation to it from the list\n- QC color change affects both the Spools table and the WIP bar chart on the Dashboard since they share the same CSS token\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Navigate to `/spools` — table loads with 200 spools from the API\n- [ ] Type in the search bar — rows filter live; clear to restore full list\n- [ ] Click a row — navigates to the spool detail page\n- [ ] Click the advance button on a non-installed spool — station updates in place without navigating away\n- [ ] Verify QC rows show amber badge and tint, not pink\n- [ ] Verify past-due dates show in amber, not red\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Create pull request"}}
